cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.CR 

This paper discusses the use of device-to-device communication to enhance IoT services in cellular networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the use of context-aware algorithms and signaling schemes, which could fall under cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also mentions the use of massive machine type communication (mMTC) and IoT devices, which could fall under cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
